],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 152714703","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/152714703/lizzie_wells-stiles"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"lizzie-hine-1867"},"HD3940":{"id":"HD3940","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mabel","last_name":"Warner","maiden_name":"Stiles","married_names":["Warner"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mabel Stiles Warner"},"birth":{"year":1878,"month":10,"day":26,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1925,"month":1,"day":6,"city":"Tucson","county":"Pima","state":"Arizona","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM293"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD3938","mother_id":"I00527"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00530","date_year":1899,"location_city":"West Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","children_ids":[]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Body shipped from Tucson to New Haven, 1925","body":"Mabel Stiles Warner died at her Tucson Arizona home on January 6, 1925 age 46, having moved there only eleven months earlier. Her body was shipped back to New Haven Connecticut by the Reilly Undertaking Company, where she joined her parents at the family plot in New Center Cemetery, North Haven."},{"category":"death","header":"Tucson home eleven months before her death","body":"She died 6 January 1925 at her South Scott Street home in Tucson Arizona — her residence of only the past eleven months. The move had likely been a health-driven relocation to desert air, common among consumptive patients of the early twentieth century.","number":2},{"category":"marriage","header":"1899 home wedding with palms and Fichtl's orchestra","body":"She married Charles Bennet Warner in 1899 at her father's West Haven home at 6 PM — described as a 'pretty home wedding' with rich white satin gown, tulle veil fastened with lilies of the valley, an improvised altar of palms and spring blossoms, and Fichtl's orchestra playing bridal music. Rev R H Gessner of Christ Episcopal Church officiated; the couple took a two-week wedding trip after a wedding supper.","number":3},{"category":"death","header":"Sister escorted body two thousand miles home","body":"Her sister Mrs Edward Stiles of Hartford was with Mabel at her Tucson death and accompanied the body home. The Reilly Undertaking Company shipped Mabel's body back to New Haven by rail — a journey of roughly two thousand miles under solo sisterly escort, for burial at New Center Cemetery.","number":4}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 126757591","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/126757591/mabel-warner"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"mabel-warner-1878"},"HD3941":{"id":"HD3941","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Stanley","middle_name":"Lorenzo","last_name":"Stiles","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Stanley Lorenzo Stiles"},"birth":{"year":1888},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1949},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD3938","mother_id":"I00527"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Lorenzo","inspired_by_id":"HD3934","description":"Middle name 'Lorenzo' carries his grandfather Isaac Lorenzo Stiles's middle name through three generations (Isaac Lorenzo Stiles → Dr. Isaac Wadsworth Stiles → Stanley Lorenzo Stiles). His uncle Frank Lorenzo Stiles (HD3939) also shares the same middle name."}],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Mother died about a year after his birth","body":"Stanley Lorenzo Stiles was born in 1888 to Dr. Isaac Wadsworth Stiles DDS and his first wife Margaret Ella Dickerman Stiles. His mother died on October 21, 1889 — approximately one year after his birth — and the death may have been childbirth-related, though the cause is not specified in available records. He was raised by his father, who eventually remarried."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Lorenzo middle name carried through three generations","body":"Stanley's middle name 'Lorenzo' was a family tradition carried across three generations: his grandfather Isaac Lorenzo Stiles, his uncle Frank Lorenzo Stiles, and Stanley himself all bore it. The repeated-middle-name pattern was characteristic of the late-nineteenth-century Stiles branch's deliberate genealogical naming conventions, preserving a distinctive ancestor's mark forward across the line."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Dual Hooker descent through both Stiles lines","body":"Stanley Lorenzo Stiles inherited dual Hooker descent paths from his father Dr. Isaac Wadsworth Stiles — who himself was double-descended through both his father (Isaac Clark Stiles branch) and his mother (Mabel Stiles Frost branch). Both lines converge at Isaac Stiles born 1729 — making Stanley a doubly-rooted Hooker descendant on his paternal side alone, with the non-Hooker maternal side adding no additional paths."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Lived to about sixty-one, marriage not documented","body":"Stanley Lorenzo Stiles died in 1949 at about age sixty-one. He was listed as 'Stanley L. Stiles surviving' in his father's February 1907 obituary at about age nineteen. Marriage and any descendants are not documented in available records."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 254712785","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/254712785/stanley_lorenzo-stiles"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"stanley-stiles-1888"},"HD3942":{"id":"HD3942","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Helen","last_name":"Stiles","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Helen Stiles"},"birth":{"year":1894,"month":10,"day":2,"city":"New Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1985,"month":12,"day":4,"city":"Chula Vista","county":"San Diego","state":"California","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM294"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD3938","mother_id":"I00528"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Orphaned at thirteen, lived to ninety-one in California","body":"Helen Stiles was twelve when her father Dr. Isaac Wadsworth Stiles died of heart disease in February 1907, and thirteen when her mother Lizzie Wells Hine Stiles died eleven months later in January 1908. She lived another seventy-seven years, dying in Chula Vista California in December 1985 age 91 and returning to New Haven for burial at Westville Cemetery."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 214810429","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/214810429/helen-stiles"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"helen-stiles-1894"},"HD3939":{"id":"HD3939","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Frank","middle_name":"Lorenzo","last_name":"Stiles","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Frank Lorenzo Stiles","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778521308/franklstiles-resized_fjvi1v.png","bio_blurb":"North Haven brickmaker and legislator"},"birth":{"year":1854,"month":7,"day":12,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1922,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM293"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD3934","mother_id":"HD3948"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00529","date_year":1887,"end_type":"death","end_year":1922,"children_ids":[]}],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Partner, then President & Treasurer","organization":"I. L. Stiles & Son Brick Company","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","end_year":1922,"notes":"Worked with father Isaac Lorenzo Stiles"},{"role":"State Representative","organization":"Connecticut General Assembly","location":"Hartford, Connecticut","start_year":1902,"notes":"Republican. Member CT state House from N"}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["state_representative"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"related_id":"HD3949","display_label":"First cousins through their Blakeslee mothers, Sophronia and Lavinia","type":"family_connection","link_text":"Anson Blakeslee Clinton"},{"related_id":"HD3928","display_label":"First cousins through Stiles brothers Isaac Lorenzo and Henry Hobart","type":"family_connection","link_text":"Mary Cyrilla Stiles Clinton"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"He took over his father’s brickyard and seat","body":"He succeeded his father as president of I. L. Stiles & Son brickmakers and, like him, won a term in the Connecticut house from North Haven in 1902. The Stileses ran the family brick business across two generations."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Stiles book (BIB008) #952"},{"label":"FindAGrave 126901004","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/126901004/frank_lorenzo-stiles"},{"label":"Political Graveyard"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"frank-stiles-1854"},"I00529":{"id":"I00529","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mary","middle_name":"A.","last_name":"Stiles","maiden_name":"Dickerman","married_names":["Stiles"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mary A. Dickerman Stiles"},"birth":{},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_th